[Ratio]
A comparison of two quantities.
.
Can be written as any of the following:
.
.  a:b
.  a/b     (where b is not 0; fractional form)
.  a to b

[Proportion]
Two equal ratios.
.
.  a/b = c/d  (where b and d are not 0)

[Cross Product Property]
The cross products formed from the two ratios in a proportion must be equal.
.
.  In a/b = c/d, ad = bc

–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––

Agata bought 20 apples at the farmers market for $12.00.

Use the proportion 20/12 = 6/x to find the amount she would have paid for
6 apples.

x...................
20 / 12 = 6 / x
20x = 12(6)
20x = 72
20x / 20 = 72 / 20
x = 3.6
x = $3.60

